You should now run &#39;preconfig&#39;, rather than &#39;configure&#39;. The  
&#39;preconfig&#39; script sets some variables and then calls &#39;configure&#39;.   
This change was made by Harry Moffat to get the configure process to  
work correctly on Sun workstations.  This will likely clear up the  
problem entirely.  If not, edit the &#39;preconfig&#39; script to set the  
PYTHON_PACKAGE variable to one of the strings &#39;full&#39;, &#39;default&#39;,  
&#39;minimal&#39;, or &#39;none&#39;.



